<section id="home">
    <h2>Homepage</h2>
    <p><strong>Title:</strong> DriveLink Ghana</p>
    <p><strong>Tagline:</strong> Fast. Trusted. Hassle-Free Car Deals.</p>
    <p>
        DriveLink Ghana is a car brokerage platform that helps individuals buy and sell cars quickly without stress.
        We connect serious buyers with verified sellers and help negotiate the best deals.
    </p>
</section>

<section id="journey">
    <h2>Entrepreneurial Journey</h2>
    
    <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Selling cars in Ghana is slow and stressful. Many sellers struggle to find serious buyers, and buyers often fear scams or overpriced vehicles.</p>
    
    <p><strong>Audience Pain Points:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Cars stay unsold for months</li>
        <li>Too many unserious buyers</li>
        <li>Lack of trust in online car deals</li>
        <li>Difficulty pricing cars correctly</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Research Validation:</strong> Through observation and real-life experience, many car owners have been trying to sell their cars for months without success. Platforms like Facebook Marketplace are crowded but inefficient.</p>
</section>

<section id="solution">
    <h2>Solution</h2>
    
    <p>
        DriveLink Ghana acts as a middleman that markets cars professionally, connects sellers to real buyers,
        and earns commission from successful deals.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Features:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Professional car listings with quality photos</li>
        <li>Targeted marketing beyond just Facebook</li>
        <li>Negotiation support for both parties</li>
        <li>Verified buyers and sellers</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Beneficiaries:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Car owners who want to sell fast</li>
        <li>Buyers looking for trusted deals</li>
        <li>Car dealers needing more exposure</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Unique Selling Points:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Focus on serious buyers only</li>
        <li>Faster sales compared to traditional platforms</li>
        <li>Local market expertise (Ghana-focused)</li>
        <li>Commission-based (no upfront risk)</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section id="prototype">
    <h2>Prototype</h2>
    
    <p><strong>Initial Idea:</strong> Start as a personal car broker using WhatsApp, social media, and contacts.</p>

    <p><strong>Development Milestones:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Phase 1: List cars from friends and contacts</li>
        <li>Phase 2: Promote cars on multiple platforms</li>
        <li>Phase 3: Build a simple website (this one)</li>
        <li>Phase 4: Launch a full marketplace platform</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Future versions will include a full website where users can list and browse cars directly.</p>
</section>

<section id="reflection">
    <h2>Reflection and Future Plans</h2>

    <p><strong>Challenges:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Competition from many informal brokers</li>
        <li>Building trust with new customers</li>
        <li>Limited marketing budget</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Lessons Learned:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Networking is key in selling cars</li>
        <li>Presentation (photos & pricing) matters a lot</li>
        <li>Trust builds sales</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Future Goals:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Launch a full car listing website/app</li>
        <li>Partner with car dealers across Ghana</li>
        <li>Introduce inspection and verification services</li>
        <li>Scale into a nationwide platform</li>
    </ul>
</section>

